      ],
      "suggestion": "Adopt a consistent wrap policy: use `%w` whenever a returned error is derived from another error, preferably via a shared helper such as `errpolicy.WrapOperation` and a small error style guide. Keep `%v` formatting only for pre-constructed literal errors and explicitly document where it is acceptable.",
